name: CBError
desc: An error that Core Bluetooth returns during Bluetooth transactions.

items.name: var errorCode: Int
items.desc: The code that identifies the error.

items.name: var errorUserInfo: [String : Any]
items.desc: A dictionary that provides details about the error.

items.name: var localizedDescription: String
items.desc: A string that contains the localized description of the error.

items.name: static var invalidHandle: CBError.Code
items.desc: The specified attribute handle is invalid.

items.name: static var outOfSpace: CBError.Code
items.desc: The device has run out of space to complete the intended operation.

items.name: static var operationCancelled: CBError.Code
items.desc: The error represents a canceled operation.

items.name: static var connectionLimitReached: CBError.Code
items.desc: The device already has the maximum number of connections.

items.name: static func != (CBError, CBError) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether two values are unequal.

items.name: enum CBError.Code
items.desc: The codes for errors that Core Bluetooth returns during Bluetooth transactions.
